<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-04T09:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-04T09:25:00-05:00" n="281" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/59: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-04T17:00:00+02:35">May 4, 1936—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 4—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>283. Situation is getting worse. Several direct shots have been fired
                                at the Legation buildings including radio station since this morning
                                and two native women in our servants’ quarters have been seriously
                                wounded.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>